def: Guidance by the hand. [Obs.] Glanvill. South.

Any one of a series of artificial blue dyestuffs, resemblingindigo in appearance, and obtained by the action of phenol on certainnitrogenous derivatives of quinone. Simple indophenol proper has notyet been isolated.
Relating to a system for transmitting power to a distance bymeans of swiftly moving ropes or cables driving grooved pulleys oflarge diameter.
High; elevated; hence, haughty; proud. [Obs.] Shak.
Being under the apex; of or pertaining to the part just belowthe apex.
To divest or deprive of deity or of a deific rank or condition.Feltham.
The middle segment of the brain; the mesencephalon. See Brain.
Resembling, or becoming to, a shepherd; pastoral; rustic. [R.]Jer. Taylor.
That which causes inhibitory action; esp., an inhibitory nerve.
